## Installation\
\
To install Cloud Sentry, follow the steps below:\
\
1. Clone the Cloud Sentry repository to your local machine.\
2. Ensure that Python 3.x is installed.\
3. Install the required Python packages by running `pip install -r requirements.txt` in the project directory.\
\
## Configuration\
\
Before using Cloud Sentry, you need to configure your AWS credentials. Follow the steps below:\
\
1. Create an IAM user with appropriate permissions.\
2. Obtain the access key ID and secret access key for the IAM user.\
3. Set the AWS credentials in the Cloud Sentry script or configure them as environment variables.\
\
## Usage\
\
To use Cloud Sentry, execute the `cloud_sentry.py` script. Follow the instructions and prompts to perform various security operations and gain valuable insights about your cloud infrastructure.\
\
## Advanced Features\
